[Notable changes from 1997 are:
5 Rotavirus infections have doubled for the period
10 Diphtheria: progress in reducing incidence continues
11 Whooping cough (pertussis): 50% more for the period
12 Scarlet fever (beta-hemolytic strep.): 50% more for the period
17 Rubella: on its way to doubling
21 Hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome: 3-fold increase
22 Hepatitis A decreasing, hep.B stable, hep.C increasing
24 Mumps: doubled in both children & adults
30 Influenza: marked drop in cases
- Mod.JW
